snippet: The death of Alexandre Strens, 24, who was working as a receptionist at the museum at the time of the attack, raises the death toll to four.
abstract: Alexandre Strens, sole surviving victim of shooting at Jewish Museum in Brussels, Belgium, dies, raising final death toll in attack by suspect Mehdi Nemmouche to four.
lead_paragraph: The death of Alexandre Strens, 24, who was working as a receptionist at the museum at the time of the attack, raises the death toll to four.

headline.main: Survivor of Attack on Jewish Museum in Brussels Dies
